@node DLGMsgs.txt "DLGGuide - DLGMsgs.txt"
@prev main

The file 'DLGMsgs.txt' can be acquired from a BBS that gathers mail in
DLG Telepro's format.  You just set up the message areas that you wish, bundle
your mail and then download it.

The format is as follows:

Message Area [-----] // Indicates the start of a new message area

[From    ] // Indicates the start of a new message
[To      ]
[Date    ]
[Subject ] // The message's subject


See Also:  @{"DLGGuide.c" link "DLGGuide.c/main"}
@endnode
